'''Gradual Integration''' is the name given to a model presented to the [[European Union]] in 2005, whereby [[Turkey]], whose potential membership in the EU has met with reluctance on the part of the European countries, would instead be able to gradually reform its economic and social systems in order to promote increased compatibility with the other members.  Since December 2004, [[Turkey]] is no longer considered a "third state", but a candidate for EU accession.<ref>http://www.wilsoncenter.org/topics/docs/Variable%20Geometries%20of%20Turkey%27s%20European%20Integration.doc</ref><ref>http://www.europesworld.org/EWSettings/Article/tabid/191/ArticleType/articleview/ArticleID/20472/Default.aspx</ref>
