{{Politics of the Republic of the Congo}}
A '''referendum on the new [[Constitution of France]]''' was held in [[Republic of the Congo|Moyen-Congo]] on 28 September 1958 as part of a [[French constitutional referendum, 1958|wider referendum]] held across the [[French Union]]. The new constitution would make the territory an autonomous republic within the [[French Community]], and was approved by 99% of voters.<ref>[http://africannewslive.com/?p=3768 1960: The year of Independence]{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} African News Live</ref> The Territorial Assembly proclaimed the [[Republic of the Congo]] on 28 November 1958,<ref>[http://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/Africa/Congo-Republic-of-the-ROC-HISTORY.html Congo, Republic of the (ROC) - History] Encyclopedia of the Nations</ref> and the country became independent two years later.
