[[Image:The Job cover Aug 2006.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Cover of ''The Job'', August 2006 issue]]
'''''The Job''''' is the official [[newspaper]] of [[London]]'s [[Metropolitan Police Service]].

The newspaper was first published on the 11 November 1967<ref name="period">{{cite web|url=http://www.metpolicehistory.co.uk/1946-to-date.html?page=2|title=Period 1946 to date|publisher=Friends of the Metropolitan Police Historical Collection|accessdate=17 January 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215061735/http://www.metpolicehistory.co.uk/1946-to-date.html?page=2|archivedate=15 February 2012|df=}}</ref> and was initially published by the Public Relations Department of the Metropolitan Police.<ref name="study">{{cite book|last=Laurie|first=Peter|title=Scotland Yard: A Study of the Metropolitan Police|url=https://www.questia.com/library/73856572/scotland-yard-a-study-of-the-metropolitan-police|accessdate=17 January 2013|year=1970|publisher=Holt, Rinehart and Winston|location=New York|page=21}}</ref> Up until March 2006, the paper was published every two weeks by Trident Communications, on behalf of the Metropolitan Police. In 2006, the contract to publish ''The Job'' was won by [[Square One Publishing]].

It is now a free monthly magazine primarily intended for officers and police staff.

